<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Step 4: The Battle</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Who knew you'd reach the final battle? As a raid leader, chances are pretty good you've committed suicide already, but on the off chance that you still live you'll now be ready to face the dragon.<br>
<br>
While people are logging in, have the groups assemble. Don't wait more than 5 minutes total from the call to log in until you are ready... if someone goes LD or doesn't make it back in, that's just too bad for them. Once enough people are there to make it happen, get it going. Everyone on the stairs, melee in front, casters in back.<br>
<br>
The first group you send in should be the heaviest melee group. Their job is to eat the first AE and get the dragon's attention. Give them 5 seconds then send in the rest of the melee, and pets. When he's down to half life, send in the casters to nuke, nuke, nuke till he's dead. If you haven't made too many mistakes up to this point, the battle itself will be pretty quick - if it's not over in the first 60 seconds, you'll probably lose.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Roles</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Warrior: Deal damage, take hits. Pretty simple.<br>
Monk: Deal damage, take hits only if you must.<br>
Rogue: Backstab, try not to get hit<br>
Ranger: Deal damage, don't pretend to be a tank unless all the real ones are dead.<br>
SK: Just like warrior, and don't forget to unleash a HT so you can get resisted.<br>
Paladin: You're a HEALER first and foremost. Your melee sucks, get used to it. Play the tank when you're out of LoH and mana.<br>
Bard: Resist songs. Don't worry about anything else, just play.<br>
Cleric: Don't let your tanks or bard die while you have mana left. Use /assist on Naggy and heal whoever he is attacking - these overlapping heals can keep people alive a long time if done right.<br>
Shaman: You're a healer for the most part... you can try to stick in a malo after tash, but you can count on having your slows resisted.<br>
Druid: Heal heal heal... you can also cast Ice when the nukes are called, if you still have mana<br>
Wizard: Stay out of combat until nukes are called then ice comet your heart out<br>
Magician: Fire pets, mmm mmm good... damage shields also good, don't bother with nukes<br>
Necromancer: Pets, heals, taps... maybe some mana feed to healers or nukers as you deem appropriate<br>
Enchanter: Pet tash and rune, nothing else you can do<br>
<br>
